Greece, EU-led Mission Agree on State Dismissals, ANA Says

-- B y   M a r i a   P e t r a k i s
-- 
2011-10-02T16:24:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-02/greece-eu-led-mission-agree-on-state-dismissals-ana-says.html
Greece ’s government and the heads of
a European Union,  International Monetary Fund  and European
Central Bank mission have reached initial agreement on plans to
place 30,000 state workers in a labor reserve system, state-run
Athens News Agency reported.  The agreement on the plan, which will reduce spending on
wages for those workers before they are dismissed, will be
presented at today’s Cabinet meeting, which will also discuss
the 2012 budget, the newswire said, without saying how it got
the information.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Maria Petrakis at 
 mpetrakis@bloomberg.net  